For the uninitiated, it can be hard to get a handle on the cult French filmmaker Chris Marker. Born Christian Fran√ßois Bouche-Villeneuve in 1921, this ‚Äúbest-known author of unknown movies‚Äù, as he once described himself, was devilishly reclusive: he rarely granted interviews, and resisted having his photograph taken, preferring instead to be represented by images of a cat.
