Even though he could be disarmingly self-deprecating (‚ÄúI make these things and people take me for Plato,‚Äù he once said with disbelief), the point of the retrospective is to suggest the scope of Marker‚Äôs creativity beyond filmmaking. We therefore encounter nearly 80 of his photographs, as well as many of the covetable travel books he edited for the Petite Plan√®te (‚ÄúSmall Planet‚Äù) series during the Fifties, designing their covers and commissioning photographers including Henri Cartier-Bresson and William Klein (Rough Guides, eat your heart out).
